Problem solving is a key component when it comes to any job IT related.

1Q- What should you do if multiple issues are happening simultaneously during troubleshooting?

1A- If multiple issues arise at the same time, it can help to isolate this issues and solve them individually. It is important
to document the process as to have something to refer to.

2Q- What should be done once a successful solution has been identified during the troubleshooting process?

2A- Once there is a successful solution, you should verify full system functionality, and then document all of the findings.

3Q- What are the benefits of documenting the entire troubleshooting process in a knowledge base?

3A- Documenting everything will help others in the future should the particular problem arise again.

4Q- Think about a technological device particularly popular in your culture or community. Imagine a scenario where issues arise: 
how would you apply CompTIA A+ troubleshooting methodology to help, while considering the end-userâ€™s cultural background?

4A- The only device I can really say that is very popular overall would be the smartphone. There are plenty of times I use
this troubleshooting methodology when solving issues for my elderly parents. It is usually something very simple, but when solving
a problem, this system helps to ensure that everything is done properly, and accurately.

